cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB

This paper is about automatic text summarization in the biomedical domain, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP, information retrieval, and text mining. 

The paper also discusses feature selection approaches and probabilistic models, which are common in machine learning and statistics. This suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also relevant sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper uses the Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) to map the input text to biomedical concepts, which involves database management and knowledge representation. This suggests that cs.DB (Databases) is a possible sub-category as well.
